────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
SECTION 1: WHAT WE ARE BUILDING
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

Project type: Real estate risk intelligence platform
Core focus: Tier-2 and Tier-3 cities in Maharashtra, India
Starting cities: Akola, Amravati (Vidarbha region)
Expansion targets: Nagpur, Wardha, Yavatmal (after quality is proven)

The product is NOT a listing portal. It is a risk, due diligence, and
anomaly intelligence platform. The core question it answers:

  "Is this project, builder, locality, or listing risky before someone
   puts serious money into it?"

This is the gap in the Indian market. Big portals (99acres, MagicBricks,
Housing.com) solve DISCOVERY. Nobody solves TRUST, RISK, and VERIFICATION
— especially outside metro cities.

────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
SECTION 2: MARKET CONTEXT
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

India real estate market size: projected ~US$970 billion by 2030 (IBEF).
PropTech is a growing category with increasing institutional deal flow.
MahaRERA has large public complaint and project datasets — a free foundation.

Competitive landscape:
  - Propstack: largest private repository of registered sale/lease/mortgage
    data in India. Claims 1M+ residential transactions, $100B+ in loans.
    Metro-focused (Mumbai, Pune, Hyderabad, Bangalore). Entire business is
    built on IGR (registration data) collected via field researchers at SRO
    offices, paid e-search portal access, and direct state govt data licensing.
    Does NOT cover Vidarbha. Akola and Amravati don't exist in their database.
  - Liases Foras: quarterly supply/demand/price research across 60+ cities.
    Consulting model, not a live data pipeline. Paid access only.
  - PropEquity: project-level data for 44 cities, subscription for PE funds.
    Metro-focused, behind paywall.
  - ANAROCK: consultancy with city-wise residential trends. Not a platform.

The gap: None of the above cover Tier-2 Maharashtra. The entire Vidarbha
region is commercially blank. That is the whitespace this project occupies.

Our edge over all of them: Three-way data cross-reference that nobody else
is doing for these cities —

  IGR actual transacted price
       vs
  RERA declared project cost/unit price
       vs
  99acres asking/listing price

A mismatch across all three is a strong anomaly and potential fraud signal.
This combination is not available from any commercial platform for Akola
or Amravati today.

────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

SOURCE 3 — IGR Maharashtra (IN PROGRESS, scraper being built)
  What: Inspector General of Registration — all registered property transactions.
  Contains: Actual sale price (consideration value), buyer/seller names,
            survey/CTS/plot number, property description, area, doc type
            (sale deed, mortgage, gift deed, etc.), registration date.
  Trust: Government. Real transacted prices. The most important data source
         for price intelligence.
  Portal: freesearchigrservice.maharashtra.gov.in (free, limited)
          pay2igr.igrmaharashtra.gov.in (paid e-search)
  Scraping method: Document number enumeration per SRO per year (sequential
                   integers). Each SRO has ~hundreds to thousands per year.
  Coverage: Data available from 1985 (Mumbai) and ~2002 (rest of Maharashtra).
  Status: Scraper under development. CAPTCHA handling is the current challenge.
  Note: Propstack's entire business model is built on this same data at scale. But currently without paid api
        its not useful so kept at side.

SOURCE 4 — e-ASR Ready Reckoner (PLANNED)
  What: Government official circle rates / guidance value by locality.
  Contains: Minimum registration value per locality per property type.
            Updated annually by state government.
  Trust: Government. Legally binding floor for stamp duty calculation.
  Value: Instant sanity check — undervalued registrations (to evade stamp duty)
         are extremely common and detectable by comparing against circle rates.
  Status: Planned. Not yet scraped.


