SECTION 6: 12-MONTH ROADMAP
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

Phase 1 — Month 1: DATA TRUST
  Goal: Clean, reliable, consistent data before selling anything
  Tasks: Fix scraper hygiene, schema stability, city_id consistency,
         confidence scoring, cleanup bad rows, finish Amravati rerun,
         get IGR scraper working reliably

Phase 2 — Month 2: SELLABLE REPORTS
  Goal: Generate clean, professional due diligence reports
  Tasks: Build PDF/HTML report generator, design report templates,
         Basic Listing Check + Project Risk Report formats

Phase 3 — Months 3–4: FIRST REVENUE
  Goal: Validate pricing and demand with real buyers
  Tasks: Manually sell 10–20 reports to local brokers, investors, homebuyers
         in Akola and Amravati. Learn what they actually want to see.

Phase 4 — Months 5–6: DASHBOARD SAAS
  Goal: Move from manual report delivery to self-serve product
  Tasks: Login system, city filters, report export, payment integration
         (Razorpay), broker dashboard with recurring subscription

Phase 5 — Months 7–9: EXPAND CITIES
  Goal: Prove the model scales beyond founding cities
  Tasks: Add Nagpur, Wardha, Yavatmal after quality checks.
         Replicate scraper + enrichment + anomaly pipeline for each city.

Phase 6 — Months 10–12: B2B / API
  Goal: Enterprise and institutional revenue
  Tasks: Pitch lenders, lawyers, valuation firms, PropTechs.
         Builder competitor intelligence product.
         API access for underwriting and data licensing.

────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
SECTION 7: WHAT NOT TO DO
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

1. Do not make ML the main selling point yet.
   The current rules-based anomaly and flag logic is already valuable if the
   data is clean. Make it reliable and explainable first. ML improves it
   later — it does not create the core value.

2. Do not use the word "fraud" in any product, report, or marketing.
   Legal and commercial risk is too high. Use safe language:
     - "risk signal"
     - "pricing anomaly"
     - "RERA concern"
     - "data inconsistency"
     - "requires verification"

3. Do not position as a listing portal.
   That market is completely saturated and dominated by portals with huge
   SEO and brand advantages. The moat is RISK and VERIFICATION, not listings.

4. Do not expand cities before quality is proven.
   Better to have excellent coverage of Akola and Amravati than shallow
   coverage of ten cities. Buyers will not trust a risk report if the data
   is incomplete or inconsistent.

5. Do not wait for perfect data before selling.
   Sell rough reports early (Phase 3). Learn from real buyers what fields
   they actually care about. Perfect later based on feedback.

6. Do not compete with Propstack on metros.
   Their moat in Mumbai, Pune, Hyderabad is deep — field teams, paid API
   access, data licensing deals. The opportunity is the 400+ cities they
   have not covered.

────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
SECTION 8: COMPETITIVE POSITIONING SUMMARY
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

Propstack parallel:
  Propstack built a ₹100B+ transaction database by systematically collecting
  IGR registration data through physical SRO presence, paid portal access, and
  govt data agreements — then layering analytics on top. Their product is
  essentially "Cotality (formerly CoreLogic) for India metros."

  We are building "Propstack for Vidarbha" — but with a key difference:
  we are adding the RERA data layer and cross-referencing it against IGR
  and listing prices for anomaly detection. Propstack has IGR but does not
  do this three-way cross-reference for fraud/risk signals.

Cotality (US) parallel:
  Cotality (formerly CoreLogic, rebranded 2024) is the 50-year-old US
  equivalent — property data, AVM (automated valuation), fraud detection,
  HPI (home price index), climate risk. Their fraud notification product,
  HPI forecasts, and scoring models are the productised versions of our
  anomaly detection, --trends, and --score pipeline respectively.

  Cotality is the long-term product roadmap reference. We are building the
  same stack, but for 400+ Indian cities that have never had it.

Financial soundness verdict:
  Good chance — but only as B2B/B2B2C real estate risk intelligence.
  The strongest wedge: "Real estate due diligence and risk intelligence
  for Tier-2/3 Maharashtra markets." Big portals focus on discovery.
  This project focuses on trust, risk, and abnormality. That is a sharper
  and largely uncontested market position.

